  "title": "奉命谋杀",
  "source_file": "data\\raw\\detectiveqa\\novel_data_en\\252-奉命谋杀-阿加莎克里斯蒂.txt",
  "chunk_index": 40,
  "summary": "Tina informs Mickey that she received a letter from Philip requesting a private meeting to ask a question that required only a yes or no answer. Upon arriving at Sun Angle, Mickey leaves Tina to meet with Philip while he goes to the garden to think. Inside, Tina encounters Mary, who is preparing coffee for Philip, and Mary mentions that Hester is returning that day. Tina then sees Hester on a landing, who explains that Dr. Calgary drove her back but has since traveled to Draymour.\n\nAs Tina walks toward the suite where the Dalantes reside, she sees Kirsten Lindstrum approaching with a tray of coffee and cookies. Kirsten enters Philip's room and suddenly gasps, dropping the tray. Tina enters the room to find Philip slumped forward in his wheelchair with a bright red, diamond-shaped stain on his white collar. Corlston observes that Philip has been stabbed to death. Tina notes that although Philip held a pen, there is no paper in front of him, suggesting the killer removed whatever he had written.\n\nTina and Corlston inform Leo and Gwendolyn of the murder. The shock causes Tina to become dizzy; she rushes outside to Mickey and faints in his arms. Hester also collapses from the shock. Mickey carries Tina to Mrs. Agg's sitting room and calls for Dr. Craig. Once Dr. Craig arrives, Corlston confirms that Philip was murdered by being stabbed in the back of the head. Mickey asks Tang to attend to the unconscious Tina.",
